Product Description

POOPH Pet Odor Eliminator - Dismantles Odors on a Molecular Level

Pooph takes stink out of the equation completely and permanently dismantling odors on a molecular level

Pooph works instantly (molecularly not enzymatically) to eliminate odors at the source so there is, quite literally, no stink OR fragrance left ... when you use Pooph, it's as if the odor was never there! And as amazingly powerful as it is, Pooph is safe for people and pets

Pooph instantly dismantles odors on a molecular basis so they never return!

Odorless/Colorless Pooph is completely colorless, odorless, and non-staining
Won't hurt people or pets Pooph is 100% safe but will get rid of any stink
Safe & Natural Pooph is a proprietary blend of minerals all of which each can be found in your average daily multivitamin
It Works Pooph works on any organic odor, so it works on much more than pet odors
1:1 As long as Pooph can reach the source of the odor and theres as much Pooph as there is stink, Pooph will get it and dismantle the odor
Longevity Poophs exact formula has been used for over 10 years getting rid of odors in North Americas top municipal waste management facilities
Works Everywhere Pooph can be used on any type of surface

Use on your pets

We recommend spraying it on a soft towel and wiping down the area on your pet that stinks. It wont hurt your pet because it is 100% safe but it will get rid of any stink

      How customer reviews and ratings work

      Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

      To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

      GA Doc
      5.0 out of 5 stars Only product we've tried that actually works.
      Reviewed in the United States on December 23, 2023
      Style: Pet Odor Eliminator - 32 oz SprayVerified Purchase
      We have had a cat or two for years. It's seems like there's always one that decides to be an idiot and start peeing anywhere except the litter box. It's never on the hardwood--always on our very thick carpet. We have tried EVERYTHING...from literally a dozen different enzyme products to home remedies like baking soda, etc. Some do work better than others but there is always SOME kind of odor still there. It might not even be cat pee odor, but we have come to associate the smell of some of the cleaners with urine, so it's almost the same thing as pee. It's disgusting and we want to kill the cat. (and yes we've tried every trick that every cat psychologist and vet recommends)

      So finally we tried this and I was a complete sceptic. The spray smells like nothing in the bottle and tastes like nothing (yes, I tasted it. I also occasionally nibbled on PlayDoh as a kid. Sue me).

      I was like, There is no way this is actually going to do anything. Well, I found an old pee spot by smelling around (and I HATE doing that), and I used a piece of chalk to circle the large pee spot. Outside the spot there was no smell. Then, inside the circle, I made a small circle (grapefruit-sized) and SOAKED the carpet there.

      The urine odor actually went away and there was a clean, almost sanitized smell left behind. And that's it! Zero pee smell. It even got rid of the smell of the last enzyme cleaner we used.

      I bought five bottles of the stuff and have gone through two already. The only issue I have is that you have to use so much of it, and this stuff ain't cheap. But frankly it's cheaper than a new carpet.

      To the people saying it doesn't work, trying pouring it on the spot instead of spraying it. Spraying it might not be delivering enough product. That was our issue at first, too.

      I don't know how this stuff works, and it's probably black magic, but I'm shocked and thrilled to be finally ridding our carpet of pee smell.

      4.0 out of 5 stars This product did not work for me: updated
      Reviewed in the United States on February 19, 2024
      Style: Pet Odor Eliminator - 32 oz SprayVerified Purchase
      First impression was low quality of packaging as the sprayer did not have a spray hole. It was solid plastic where the liquid should come out.

      I drilled out the hole but then the spray came out like a squirt gun rather than a spray/mist.

      I got a blanket from my dog crate and soaked it with POOPH. It still smelled like dog. I then sprayed my hands and they still smelled like the blanket. So, it didn't work at all for me.

      Update: subsequent to the above experience, we found an old urine stain on our mattress cover. It was yellow and still had a bad odor. I soaked it with POOPH and the odor vanished. The yellow stain had retreated to a wide ring around the edge of the pooled POOPH in the sprayed area (the cover is waterproof).

      So, I ended up washing the whole cover (California King) to get rid of the yellow area.

      Anyway, it seems to work on urine but not so much on general dog stink that might rub off on a blanket.

      3.0 out of 5 stars Works but has limitations.
      Reviewed in the United States on April 7, 2024
      Style: Pet Odor Eliminator - 32 oz SprayVerified Purchase
      We purchased this to apply to a leather chair to remove a cat urine issue. The product appears to work well on hard surfaces with limited porosity. The product removed the odor initially but it returned a short time later. Some of the urine may have made it to the fabric underside of the seat cushion. The product states that it may not work as well on areas that odors soak into. It has to make direct contact to eliminate the orders. Did not work well in our instance. After multiple treatments, it has diminished the odor somewhat. But it returns each time. Not as bad as before but still a faint smell remains.
